    <p><span style="line-height: 1.538em;">What is clean code? At last night's </span><a href="http://www.meetup.com/SFDUG-San-Francisco-Drupal-Users-group/" style="line-height: 1.538em;">SFDUG</a><span style="line-height: 1.538em;"> I gave a brief introduction to two complexity metrics—cyclomatic complexity and npath complexity—and how we can use these metrics to gain insight into the readability and maintainability of one's code.</span></p><br />
<br />
<p><a href="http://phpmd.org">PHPMD</a> is a tool that analyzes and warns about overly complex code. The metrics alone are useful, but having a tool to crunch the numbers automatically is extremely handy. In addition to PHPMD, I recommended using a plugin for one's editor and/or IDE, such as <a href="https://github.com/scrooloose/syntastic">Syntastic</a> for Vim.</p>
